  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper we investigate a new class of implicit–explicit (IMEX) two-step methods of Peer type for systems of ordinary differential equations with both non-stiff and stiff parts included in the source term. An extrapolation approach based on already computed stage values is applied to construct IMEX methods with favourable stability properties. Optimised IMEX-Peer methods of order <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></math> , are given as result of a search algorithm carefully designed to balance the size of the stability regions and the extrapolation errors. Numerical experiments and a comparison to other implicit–explicit methods are included.</subfield>
